Compare Models ⚖️
Logistic Regression 🔀
So far we examined the performance of a logistic regression for our population. Logistic Regression got many benefits - it’s used for over a hundred years and it’s explainable. In terms of prediction Logistic Regression is not optimal.
Tree Model 🌲
Tree Models are extremely popular in Machine Learning, generally they are all based on Decision Trees. These kind of models are considered to be “Black Boxes” because you don’t really know (or even care) what they do, but you know that they are doing it well. How do you know that? You’ve guessed it - Performance Metrics!
Random Guess 🙈
Maybe you are familiar with Emile Borel quote in his book ()

If an army of monkeys were strumming on typewriters they might write all the books in the British Museum.

It doesn’t mean that you want a monkey to make a prediction, but for education purposes we will give him (or for the rbinom() function) a chance to compete with our man-made model. In order to be fair we will tell the monkey the prevalence of the population and set it as the p parameter in the binomial distribution.
